Mary BUCKLEY, Appellant, v. John D. NAGLE, as Commissioner of Immigration for the Port of San Francisco, California, Appellee. No. 6358. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 12, 1931.

Before RUDKIN and WILBUR, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Ordered appeal dismissed pursuant to motion' of appellee, and for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
